                <note rend="inline" type="source">500. A 4e/108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-02T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 2—11:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>403. Your 235, September 27, noon. Foreign Office note dated September 30th
                    quotes telegram from Chairman Shanghai Tariff Revision Conference stating that
                    conference in full meeting has approved revised import tariff prepared by it,
                    and passed resolution that new tariff shall be promulgated October 1st and go
                    into effect December 1st, 1922, “provided that all articles whose shipment for
                    China was made prior to December 1st, 1922, shall pay import duty in accordance
                    with former tariff.” Telegram adds that delegates of different Nations are
                    requesting their Governments to give their agreement to execution of this
                    procedure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
